 "\"DIRECT MATERIAL COST\":\"Direct material cost refers to the cost of raw materials that are directly used in the production of a product. This cost is a part of the total cost calculation in both traditional absorption costing and the ABC system.\"", "\"DIRECT LABOR COST\":\"Direct labor cost refers to the wages and salaries of employees who are directly involved in the production of a product. This cost is included in the total cost calculation in both traditional absorption costing and the ABC system.\"", "\"FIXED OVERHEAD COST\":\"Fixed overhead cost\" refers to the indirect costs that do not vary with the level of production. These costs include rent, utilities, salaries of administrative staff, and insurance. In traditional absorption costing, fixed overhead costs are allocated based on a single cost driver, such as machine hours.", "\"MULTIPLE COST DRIVERS\":\"Multiple cost drivers refer to the various factors that cause overhead costs to be incurred, such as machine setups, production runs, and quality inspections. In the ABC approach, overhead costs are allocated based on these multiple cost drivers.\"", "\"LABOR HOURS\":\"Labor hours refer to the total hours worked by employees directly involved in the production process. In traditional absorption costing, labor hours can be used as the single cost driver to allocate overhead costs.\"", "\"PREPARING THE OPERATING THEATRE\":\"Preparing the operating theatre is an activity in ABC where the cost is driven by the number of operations. The cost does not vary significantly between different types of operations.\"", "\"ACTIVITY OF ANAESTHETIST\":\"Activity of anaesthetist is an activity in ABC where the cost is driven by the number of operations, calculated separately for those requiring a general anaesthetic and those requiring only local anaesthetics.\"", "\"ANAESTHETIC DRUGS\":\"Anaesthetic drugs is an activity in ABC where the cost is driven by the time taken from entering the anaesthetic room until entering the recovery room.\"", "\"ACTIVITY OF THE PHYSICIAN\":\"Activity of the physician is an activity in ABC where the cost is driven by the time taken from initial incision to closure of incision on completion of surgery.\"", "\"CONSUMABLE ITEMS DURING SURGERY\":\"Consumable items during surgery is an activity in ABC where the cost is driven by an itemised list of consumables used during surgery, captured by a bar-coding device.\"", "\"OVERHEAD ACTIVITY\":\"Overhead activity is an activity in ABC where the cost is driven by a charge for management administration and staff training.\"", "\"MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTING\":\"Management accounting is concerned with preparing and presenting accounting information to assist management in planning, controlling, and making decisions.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}